hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews:
Another good Mercure property, based in an old building close to Gare de Lyon railway station, with staff offering a friendly welcome.

It's Paris, so the room was small - but clean and comfortable. Good shower, albeit a bit of a climb in. Wifi worked reliably for business purposes.

Plenty of cafes/bistros etc nearby.

Ironing board needs a cover!

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: Convenient location to Gare de Lyon with very nice rooms and customer service is the best. Very likely to come back because of the welcome and help from Antonio and Arthur who made sure that the rooms, stay, check-in, breakfast and, transportation worked out the best. Room was quiet, fresh and had enough closet space for the baggage and no problems with using the lift and walking around the Gare de Lyon area. All friends and family were able to find the place easily. The best part was the very warm and authentic welcome from Antonio every evening who made sure we were happy, safe and pleased with our stay. He made sure to show every part of the Accor brand especially guest service/passion to make a difference, respect and trust. Many people we met during the time in the reception area but Antonio and Arthur were the very best. Anticipate a future stay and warm welcome there!

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: The Mercure's location is excellent, with Gare De Lyon located just a three minute walk away. The rooms are small (not as big as the photos suggest) but they are well appointed and the bathroom was good (I particularly liked the honey shower gel). Be careful not to slip getting in/out of the shower! The breakfast was very good and I loved the Parisian treats. I am learning French and the staff allowed me to practice my language skills with them. Overall a positive experience.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: Location and hotel were great! Best stay in Paris I ever had so far. Staff were super friendly and helpful in every occasion. Breakfast was excellent. Rooms were quite small across the whole building but that's just how Paris is in general.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: I really enjoyed my stay in this cozy parisian hotel! From the moment we arrived we felt at home! Rooms aren't huge but they have all the amenities needed for our stay! The hotel is also really close to the train station which was perfect for our Paris tours. A special thanks to the reception team who was amazing during our stay.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews:
This hotel was the best hotel I’ve stayed in all my travels, they couldn’t of been more helpful and friendly!
Thank you so much for the best stay and a special thank you to Gianantonio for going the extra mile and making us feel very comfortable. 😄

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews:
The first impression when you walk in is not promising. There’s no reception desk. If you look around there are a couple of women sitting on lounges with laptops who turned out to be the reception clerks. Who’s stupid idea was this? When the reception is busy they have to use the adjoining bar for their laptops and to access supplies. It’s a very unprofessional way to greet guests.

Things got worse when we were assigned our room on the third floor and only then were we informed that the lift doesn’t stop at the third floor! They should’ve informed us first. Since we had heavy suitcases, it would’ve been nice if they could have assigned us a room with a working lift.

Our room was setup to give access to the adjoining room (which we didn’t request). To enter our room, we had to manoeuvre our luggage through 3 heavy doors, none of which stay open. Once we finally got in, the room was small but fine. Comfortable bed. The insulated windows kept out traffic noise. The shower screen doesn’t have a door so that the bathroom floor got very wet and slippery when I showered. I had to use 2 towels to dry it.

One the plus side, the hotel is very close to Gare de Lyon and nearby restaurants.

Be careful when booking, not to confuse this hotel with the Mercure Gare de Lyon TGV which is directly adjoining the station.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews:
Beautiful building, great location with very friendly and helpful staff.
Highly recommend as a great Paris location.
The building was beautifully renovated in 2019.
We didn’t have breakfast, but the breakfast area is quite large for a boutique hotel.
We have been to Paris many times, and will definitely return to this hotel.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: Our time here was wonderful! Gian Antonio was so helpful, kind, and funny, and he always greeted us with a smile. His English was excellent, and whether he was answering our questions, making coffee, recommending our new favorite restaurant in Paris (Spiga, right across the street) or remembering my birthday, he always went above and beyond. The room we had was neat and clean, and the whole hotel is full of the Parisien charm we were looking for. We want to give a “merci beaucoup” to the Mercure Gare de Lyon Opéra Bastille Hôtel. We definitely recommend it!

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews:
Had a 2-night stay there after a 27h journey back to France. We arrived 1h earlier than checkin time so room was not ready (which is ok). But the actual checkin experience was not really enjoyable. No checkin desk, just ppl sitting in couches with laptops, 4 hotel staff there but 3 were enjoying a smoke outside whilst leaving one new staff alone to deal with the fact that after checkin time kicked in, room was still not ready.
The room itself is fairly small but that’s fine for the price we paid. However, the level of available amenities was quite disappointing (only 1 very tiny desk and 1 small armchair). The bathroom was rather nice (with a bathtub) but the exhaust was not powerful enough and the only way to avoid a wet damp smell was to leave the bathroom ajar.
The bed was really nice though.

I cannot speak about the food as I had my breakfasts in nearby cafes and lunch/dinner in other areas in Paris.
If you go from the hotel back to Bastille area, you will find a nice place on the way called “Le Botaniste” which serves nice food and excellent cocktails.
Overall, if you are looking for a place to just sleep while you visit Paris, this place is for you.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: We missed our connection to Barcelona and had this hotel organised by SNCF. Thrilled with the hotel, the staff, who were very welcoming, and the location. Would visit again. Thanks very much. Nick and Ruth and family from UK.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: We were completely satisfied with this hotel. It's located next to the railway station but it's quiet and clean in this location. The staff is extremely friendly. The hotel is extremely cool and exceeded our expectations. Special thanks for Antonio .

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: The location of the hotel is good for metro access but perhaps not the best for families. The rooms are small and cozy, although we faced a bit of issue with the water in the shower finding it's way to the floor. The reception and the breakfast staff was outstanding, and breakfast was very decent too. The little lobby makes you feel chilled out!

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: Very good service, breakfast was good, and super friendly receptionists! I recommend this hotel if you are a tourist. Rooms were nice, and bathrooms were also clean. Very small hotel and rooms, but I enjoyed staying here.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: Our room was perfect for us and our Granddaughter. We were checked in by Antonio ( I hope I have the name correct) Antonio was extraordinary, very polite and welcoming, everything you want assisting you at check in and during your stay. A courteous professional.

hotel: Mercure Paris Gare de Lyon Opera Bastille
reviews: Stayed here with my girlfriend in January of last, and thoroughly enjoyed it! Staff were very welcoming and the service was excellent. The hotel is quite small in size but very cosy. Located in Bastille, the hotel is near a number of metro stations and Gare de Lyon itself. Makes it very accessible to all of Paris! The room was small but nothing we didn’t expect. The beds were comfy, shower worked perfect, but only lacked a nice view of the city around us. Would recommend here for anyone visiting Paris!
